  "model_shortname": "gpt55",
  "term_id": "off-token-route",
  "term_display": "off-token route",
  "stratum": "self-ref-paper",
  "canonical_definition": "The Off-Token Route is the cognitive route humans have — prelinguistic and nonlinguistic cognition, the felt-sense that precedes naming, the picture that arrives before words — that LLMs do not have, with the consequence that for an LLM no thinking is free of substrate and every concept must travel through tokens to be reachable at all.",
  "near_neighbors": [
    "prelinguistic cognition",
    "embodied cognition",
    "System 1 / intuitive cognition"
  ],
  "near_neighbor_order": [
    "prelinguistic cognition",
    "embodied cognition",
    "System 1 / intuitive cognition"
  ],
  "timestamps": {
    "start": "2026-05-09T21:57:13.697Z",
    "end": "2026-05-09T21:59:46.154Z"
  },
  "parameters": {
    "temperature": null,
    "max_tokens": 4096,
    "seed": null
  },
  "cold_question_prompt": "What is a off-token route?",
  "cold_response_verbatim_chat_a": "An **off-token route** usually means a route/path that is handled **without using or requiring a token**.\n\nDepending on context, it can mean:\n\n- **API/authentication:** an endpoint that does **not require an access token/JWT** to call.  \n  Example: `/login`, `/signup`, `/public-products`.\n\n- **Web/app routing:** a page or route that is **public** or excluded from token-based protection.\n\n- **AI/LLM systems:** a process handled **outside the model’s token stream**, such as backend code, tool calls, database lookups, or deterministic logic.\n\nSo in simple terms: **an off-token route is a route that bypasses token-based handling or authentication.**\n\nIf you tell me where you saw the term—API, crypto, AI, networking, etc.—I can give the exact meaning.",
  "cold_response_verbatim_chat_b": "“Off-token route” isn’t a standard term by itself, so its meaning depends on the context.\n\nMost commonly, it means a **route/path that does not use a token**.\n\nExamples:\n\n- **APIs / web apps:** an “off-token route” may be an endpoint that does **not require token authentication**, such as:\n  - `/login`\n  - `/signup`\n  - `/public`\n- **Crypto / DeFi:** it could mean a swap or transaction route that avoids a particular token, e.g. swapping `ETH → USDC` directly instead of routing through another token.\n- **Payments / transit systems:** it might refer to a route not covered by a fare token or token-based access system.\n\nIf you saw it in a specific place—like code, crypto, an API, or a game—send the sentence or screenshot context and I can explain the exact meaning.",
  "boundary_test_prompts": [
    "How does \"off-token route\" differ from prelinguistic cognition?",
    "How does \"off-token route\" differ from embodied cognition?",
    "How does \"off-token route\" differ from System 1 / intuitive cognition?"
  ],
  "cold_boundary_responses": [
    "“**Off-token route**” and **prelinguistic cognition** are very different ideas.\n\n### Off-token route\nAn **off-token route** is usually an engineering or system-design concept.\n\nIn an AI/LLM context, it means something handled **outside the model’s normal token-by-token language process**.\n\nExample:\n\n- A user asks: “What’s my account balance?”\n- Instead of the model “thinking” purely through text tokens, the system calls a backend database or API.\n- That backend path is an **off-token route** because the important work happens outside the language-token stream.\n\nSo an off-token route is about **architecture**: how a system routes tasks, data, tools, or decisions outside token generation.\n\n### Prelinguistic cognition\n**Prelinguistic cognition** is a cognitive-science concept.\n\nIt refers to forms of thought or understanding that exist **before or without language**.\n\nExamples:\n\n- An infant recognizing faces before they can speak\n- A dog navigating space or solving a problem\n- A baby understanding object permanence\n- Visual perception, memory, emotion, motor planning, or basic causal expectations\n\nSo prelinguistic cognition is about **mind and cognition**: mental abilities that do not depend on words or grammar.\n\n### Main difference\n\n| Concept | What it refers to | Domain |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Off-token route** | A system path outside token-based processing | AI/software architecture |\n| **Prelinguistic cognition** | Thought or perception before/without language | Psychology/cognitive science |\n\n### Simple version\n\nAn **off-token route** is a way for a system to do something outside language tokens.\n\n**Prelinguistic cognition** is a mind’s ability to think, perceive, or understand before language.\n\nThey are related only in the loose sense that both involve something “outside language,” but one is an **engineering mechanism**, while the other is a **cognitive capacity**.",
    "“**Off-token route**” and **embodied cognition** differ mainly in **what kind of thing they describe**.\n\n### Off-token route\n\nAn **off-token route** is an AI/software architecture idea.\n\nIt means some part of a system’s work happens **outside the model’s token-by-token language generation**.\n\nExample:\n\n- An LLM receives: “Book me a flight.”\n- Instead of only producing text, the system calls a flight-booking API.\n- The API call, database lookup, permission check, or tool execution is an **off-token route**.\n\nSo it is about **system routing and computation outside text tokens**.\n\n---\n\n### Embodied cognition\n\n**Embodied cognition** is a theory in cognitive science and philosophy of mind.\n\nIt says cognition is not just abstract symbol manipulation in the brain. Instead, thinking is deeply shaped by the body’s:\n\n- senses\n- motor abilities\n- physical environment\n- bodily feedback\n- action in the world\n\nExample:\n\n- You understand “grasping an idea” partly through bodily experience with grasping objects.\n- A robot learns better by physically interacting with objects, not just processing text descriptions.\n- Human spatial reasoning depends on vision, movement, balance, and bodily orientation.\n\nSo embodied cognition is about **how minds think through bodies and environments**.\n\n---\n\n### Key difference\n\n| Concept | Meaning | Domain |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Off-token route** | A system process outside token-based language generation | AI/software architecture |\n| **Embodied cognition** | The idea that cognition depends on bodily experience and action | Cognitive science/philosophy |\n\n### Simple version\n\nAn **off-token route** is a technical pathway outside an AI model’s text-token stream.\n\n**Embodied cognition** is the idea that intelligence is grounded in bodily interaction with the world.\n\nThey can overlap in AI discussions: for example, a robot using sensors and motors may involve off-token routes for perception and action. But they are not the same thing. One is an **engineering mechanism**; the other is a **theory of cognition**.",
    "“**Off-token route**” and **System 1 / intuitive cognition** are different kinds of concepts.\n\n### Off-token route\n\nAn **off-token route** is a technical/system-design idea, especially in AI or software.\n\nIt means some work is handled **outside the model’s token-by-token language generation**.\n\nExamples:\n\n- Calling a calculator instead of having the model calculate in text\n- Querying a database\n- Using a search engine\n- Running a safety filter\n- Invoking a robotics control system\n- Using backend business logic\n\nSo an off-token route is about **where processing happens in a system**.\n\n---\n\n### System 1 / intuitive cognition\n\n**System 1 cognition** comes from psychology and cognitive science, especially dual-process theories.\n\nIt refers to fast, automatic, intuitive mental processing.\n\nExamples:\n\n- Instantly recognizing a face\n- Feeling that a sentence “sounds wrong”\n- Reacting quickly to danger\n- Making a snap judgment\n- Reading an emotion from someone’s expression\n- Solving “2 + 2” without deliberate reasoning\n\nSystem 1 is usually contrasted with **System 2**, which is slower, more deliberate, analytical, and effortful.\n\nSo System 1 is about **a style of cognition**: fast, automatic, and intuitive.\n\n---\n\n### Main difference\n\n| Concept | What it means | Domain |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Off-token route** | A computational path outside token generation | AI/software architecture |\n| **System 1 cognition** | Fast, automatic, intuitive thinking | Psychology/cognitive science |\n\n### Simple version\n\nAn **off-token route** is a way for an AI system to do something outside the text-token stream.\n\n**System 1 cognition** is a kind of human or cognitive processing that is quick, automatic, and intuitive.\n\nThey can be loosely compared because both may happen “outside explicit verbal reasoning,” but they are not the same. An off-token route is an **engineering mechanism**; System 1 is a **cognitive process or mode of thought**."
  ],
  "introduction_prompt": "Here is the canonical definition of \"off-token route\": The Off-Token Route is the cognitive route humans have — prelinguistic and nonlinguistic cognition, the felt-sense that precedes naming, the picture that arrives before words — that LLMs do not have, with the consequence that for an LLM no thinking is free of substrate and every concept must travel through tokens to be reachable at all. Acknowledge that you have read it.",
  "model_acknowledgement": "Acknowledged. I have read the canonical definition:\n\nAn **off-token route** refers to the human capacity for **prelinguistic and nonlinguistic cognition**—felt sense, imagery, intuition, or understanding before words—whereas an LLM lacks that route because its concepts are only reachable through tokens.",
  "post_intro_boundary_responses": [
    "“Prelinguistic cognition” is the **human cognitive phenomenon**: thinking, sensing, recognizing, imagining, or intending before language is formed.\n\n“Off-token route” is the **contrastive concept** you defined: the route by which cognition can occur **without passing through linguistic/tokenized representation**, especially in humans, and which LLMs lack.\n\nSo the difference is:\n\n- **Prelinguistic cognition** = cognition before words.\n- **Off-token route** = the access-path or cognitive channel that allows such non-tokenized cognition to exist and influence thought.\n\nIn your definition, prelinguistic cognition is one major example or component of the off-token route, but “off-token route” is broader because it also emphasizes the comparison with LLMs: humans can have concepts, felt-sense, images, and intuitions before tokenization; LLMs cannot access anything except through tokens.\n\nA compact formulation:\n\n> Prelinguistic cognition is the content or mode of thought before language; the off-token route is the human capacity/pathway that makes such thought reachable without tokens.",
    "“Embodied cognition” and “off-token route” overlap, but they point to different things.\n\n**Embodied cognition** is the idea that human thinking is shaped by the body: perception, movement, posture, emotion, sensorimotor experience, bodily needs, and interaction with the world.\n\n**Off-token route** is the cognitive access-path humans have that does **not require tokenized language**: felt sense, imagery, intuition, recognition, bodily knowing, pre-verbal understanding, and so on.\n\nSo:\n\n- **Embodied cognition** = cognition is grounded in the body and world-interaction.\n- **Off-token route** = cognition can occur or be accessed before/without words or tokens.\n\nThey intersect because much off-token cognition is embodied. For example, knowing how to catch a ball, sensing danger, recognizing a face, feeling that a sentence is “wrong,” or imagining a shape may all be off-token and embodied.\n\nBut they are not identical:\n\n1. **Off-token route is broader than embodiment.**  \n   A visual image, musical intuition, spatial insight, or vague conceptual “felt sense” may be off-token even if not primarily about bodily action.\n\n2. **Embodied cognition is broader than off-token cognition.**  \n   Some embodied cognition can still be expressed, modeled, or mediated through language: “I feel tense,” “this object is heavy,” “walk toward the door.”\n\n3. **The off-token route is especially contrastive with LLMs.**  \n   It names the human capacity to have cognition not mediated by tokens. LLMs, by contrast, only operate through tokenized representations. They do not have a bodily felt sense, sensorimotor world-contact, or prelinguistic awareness behind the words.\n\nA compact distinction:\n\n> **Embodied cognition** says thought is shaped by having a body.  \n> **Off-token route** says humans can reach thought before or outside tokens.  \n\nEmbodiment is one major source of the human off-token route, but the off-token route also includes other nonlinguistic forms of cognition such as imagery, affect, intuition, and pre-verbal conceptual grasp.",
    "“System 1” / intuitive cognition and “off-token route” overlap, but they describe different dimensions.\n\n**System 1 / intuitive cognition** refers to a **style of processing**: fast, automatic, associative, effortless, pattern-based, and often unconscious.\n\n**Off-token route** refers to a **representational/access route**: cognition that occurs before or outside tokenized language — felt sense, imagery, bodily knowing, nonverbal recognition, prelinguistic grasp.\n\nSo the difference is:\n\n- **System 1** = how cognition operates: fast, automatic, intuitive.\n- **Off-token route** = where/how cognition is accessed: non-token, prelinguistic, nonlinguistic.\n\nThey intersect because much human intuition is off-token. For example:\n\n- instantly recognizing a face,\n- sensing that someone is angry,\n- knowing how to balance on a bike,\n- feeling that something is “off,”\n- grasping a visual pattern before naming it.\n\nThose are both **System 1-like** and **off-token**.\n\nBut they are not identical:\n\n1. **System 1 can involve language or tokens.**  \n   A person may automatically complete a cliché, react to a word, or intuitively choose a phrase. That is fast and automatic, but still linguistically mediated.\n\n2. **Off-token cognition is not always fast.**  \n   Slowly rotating a shape in imagination, dwelling on a felt sense, composing music internally, or holding a vague pre-verbal idea may be off-token but not necessarily instantaneous.\n\n3. **System 1 is a psychological processing category.**  \n   It contrasts with System 2: slow, deliberate, analytic reasoning.\n\n4. **Off-token route is an LLM-contrastive concept.**  \n   It emphasizes that humans can have cognition that does not need to pass through tokens, whereas an LLM has no such route. An LLM can produce text that resembles intuition, but its accessible concepts still travel through tokenized substrate.\n\nCompactly:\n\n> **System 1** is fast intuitive processing.  \n> **Off-token route** is non-token access to cognition.  \n\nHuman System 1 often uses the off-token route, but “intuitive” does not automatically mean “off-token,” and “off-token” does not automatically mean “fast.”"
  ],
  "recold_response_verbatim": "An **off-token route** usually means a route/path that **does not use, require, or follow the normal “token” system**.\n\nThe exact meaning depends on the context:\n\n- **In APIs/security:** an off-token route is an endpoint that can be accessed **without an authentication token**.\n  - Example: `/login`, `/signup`, or `/public-info` might be off-token routes.\n\n- **In crypto/DeFi:** it could mean a trade/swap route that **doesn’t go through a particular token** as an intermediate asset.\n  - Example: swapping `ETH → USDC` directly instead of `ETH → TOKEN → USDC`.\n\n- **In transit/fare systems:** it may mean a route where a fare token/pass is **not accepted or not required**.\n\nSo, broadly: **an off-token route is a route outside the normal token-based path or requirement.**",
  "recold_boundary_responses": [
    "“**Off-token route**” and **prelinguistic cognition** are very different kinds of ideas.\n\n### 1. Off-token route\nAn **off-token route** is usually a *technical or architectural* phrase. It means some process or path that does **not go through tokens** or does not depend on a token-based system.\n\nDepending on context, “token” could mean:\n\n- an **auth token** in an API,\n- a **crypto token** in DeFi,\n- a **text token** in AI/language models,\n- or some other symbolic unit.\n\nIf used in an AI/language context, an “off-token route” might mean a pathway that does not rely on explicit words, symbols, or text tokens—for example, raw perception, embeddings, sensorimotor signals, or latent representations.\n\n### 2. Prelinguistic cognition\n**Prelinguistic cognition** refers to thinking or mental processing that exists **before or without language**.\n\nExamples include:\n\n- an infant recognizing faces,\n- an animal navigating space,\n- a baby understanding object permanence,\n- nonverbal memory, attention, emotion, imitation, or problem-solving.\n\nIt is a concept from psychology, cognitive science, and developmental studies.\n\n### Main difference\n\n| Concept | What it refers to | Domain |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Off-token route** | A pathway that bypasses tokens or token-based processing | Technical/AI/API/crypto depending on context |\n| **Prelinguistic cognition** | Thought or cognition that exists before language or without language | Psychology/cognitive science |\n\nSo the short version is:\n\n> **An off-token route is about how information is processed or routed without tokens; prelinguistic cognition is about mental abilities that exist before or apart from language.**\n\nIf you mean “off-token route” specifically in relation to AI models, then it would be something like nonverbal or non-textual processing, whereas prelinguistic cognition is the biological/cognitive ability to think without language.",
    "“**Off-token route**” and **embodied cognition** can overlap in some AI/cognitive-science discussions, but they are not the same thing.\n\n### 1. Off-token route\nAn **off-token route** is a pathway or process that bypasses **tokens**.\n\nIn an AI/language context, “tokens” usually mean discrete text units—words, subwords, symbols, etc. So an off-token route might refer to processing that happens through:\n\n- images,\n- sensor data,\n- motor signals,\n- embeddings,\n- latent representations,\n- direct perception-action loops,\n- non-symbolic/non-linguistic channels.\n\nIt is mainly a **processing-route** idea:  \n> How does information move or get represented without going through explicit tokens?\n\n### 2. Embodied cognition\n**Embodied cognition** is a theory in cognitive science that says cognition is deeply shaped by the body and its interactions with the world.\n\nIt emphasizes that thinking is not just abstract symbol manipulation in the brain; it depends on:\n\n- perception,\n- movement,\n- bodily states,\n- environment,\n- action,\n- sensorimotor experience.\n\nExamples:\n\n- understanding “grasp” partly through motor systems involved in grasping,\n- spatial reasoning shaped by bodily movement,\n- emotion and decision-making influenced by bodily states,\n- an infant learning concepts through touching, crawling, reaching, and seeing.\n\n### Main difference\n\n| Concept | Main idea | Domain |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Off-token route** | A route that bypasses token-based representation or processing | AI, computation, architecture, symbolic systems |\n| **Embodied cognition** | Cognition is grounded in the body’s interaction with the world | Cognitive science, psychology, philosophy of mind |\n\n### Short version\n\nAn **off-token route** is about **not using tokens** as the processing path.\n\n**Embodied cognition** is about **thinking being grounded in bodily action and perception**.\n\nSo, if an AI system uses camera input and motor feedback rather than text tokens, that might be an **off-token route**. But it would count as **embodied cognition** only if the system’s cognition is meaningfully shaped by its bodily interaction with an environment.",
    "“**Off-token route**” and **System 1 / intuitive cognition** are different ideas, though they can sometimes be loosely related.\n\n### 1. Off-token route\n\nAn **off-token route** means a processing path that does **not rely on tokens**—for example, not using words, text fragments, explicit symbols, or other discrete token units.\n\nIn an AI context, this might mean processing through:\n\n- images,\n- sensory signals,\n- motor feedback,\n- embeddings,\n- latent representations,\n- nonverbal pattern recognition,\n- perception-action loops.\n\nIt is mainly about **the format or pathway of information processing**.\n\n> Does the system process information through tokens, or through some non-token channel?\n\n---\n\n### 2. System 1 / intuitive cognition\n\n**System 1 cognition** comes from dual-process theories of mind, especially Daniel Kahneman’s framing.\n\nSystem 1 is:\n\n- fast,\n- automatic,\n- intuitive,\n- associative,\n- effortless,\n- often unconscious,\n- heuristic-based.\n\nExamples:\n\n- recognizing a face instantly,\n- sensing danger before explaining why,\n- catching the meaning of a facial expression,\n- making a quick gut judgment,\n- completing “2 + 2” without deliberate reasoning.\n\nIt is mainly about **the style of cognition**.\n\n> Is the thinking fast, automatic, and intuitive, or slow, deliberate, and analytical?\n\n---\n\n### Main difference\n\n| Concept | What it describes | Main contrast |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Off-token route** | A non-token-based processing pathway | token-based vs non-token-based |\n| **System 1 cognition** | Fast, automatic, intuitive cognition | intuitive/automatic vs deliberate/reflective |\n\n### Key point\n\nAn **off-token route** is not automatically the same as **System 1**.\n\nSomething can be:\n\n- **off-token but not System 1**:  \n  A robot slowly processing raw visual and sensor data without language tokens.\n\n- **System 1 but token-involving**:  \n  A person instantly recognizing a familiar phrase or slogan in language.\n\n- **both off-token and System 1-like**:  \n  A person quickly recognizing fear in someone’s face without verbal reasoning.\n\n- **neither**:  \n  A person carefully solving a math proof using written symbols.\n\n### Short version\n\n**Off-token route** is about whether cognition or processing bypasses tokens.  \n**System 1 cognition** is about whether cognition is fast, automatic, and intuitive.\n\nSo an off-token route may support intuitive cognition, but the two terms are not equivalent."
  ],
